com.versant.fund
Class FundQueryResult

java.lang.Object
  com.versant.fund.AbstractQueryResult
      com.versant.fund.FundQueryResult

public class FundQueryResult
extends AbstractQueryResult

Instances of this class are created by the com.versant.fund.FundQuery.execute() method. The instance encapsulates the result set of that query. Not all handles in that result set are necessarily loaded into memory at the creation time but can be loaded deferred as requested.

Since:
7.0.0
See Also:
FundQuery

next

public Handle[] next(int size)
Returns up to size handles from the result set into an array. If there are less handles then size left in the result set the array will contain the remaining handles left in the QueryResult.

If there were no handles left in the query result, an empty array is returned.

Parameters:
size - - The maximum number of handles returned in the array.
Returns:
An array of Handle instances of the result set. The length of the array is at most size.

nextAll

public Handle[] nextAll()
Returns the remaining handles in the result set. If no calls to next(), next(size) or nextAll() have been made before, this method will return all handles in the original result set.

If there were no handles left in the query result, an empty array is returned.

Returns:
An array of Handle instances of the result set.

nextRow

public java.lang.Object nextRow()

Returns:

nextRows

public java.lang.Object[] nextRows(int size)
Returns up to size rows from the result set into an array. If there are less rows then size left in the result set the array will contain the remaining rows left in the QueryResult.

If there were no rows left in the query result, an empty array is returned.

Parameters:
size - - The maximum number of rows returned in the array.
Returns:
An array of Object[] instances of the result set. If there is only one column selected than the object of appropriate type is returned for each row. The length of the array is at most size.

allRows

public java.lang.Object[] allRows()
Returns the remaining rows in the result set. If no calls to nextRow(), nextRows(size) or allRows() have been made before, this method will return all rows in the original result set.

If there were no rows left in the query result, an empty array is returned.

Returns:
An array of Object instances of the result set.
